pr_review_comment_body:
Nope not quiet it doesn't set

last_stride_y = stride_y;
last_stride_x = stride_x;
last_padding_y = padding_y;
last_padding_x = padding_x;

 that's the only "setup" the CPU implementation seems to do.

You could call this one in the other one to make it nicer and reduce code duplication yes. 
I thought about that but left it out for now.

The reason why is there is a much larger difference in the CUDA version but I have to keep the same signatures as interface between the two have to stay the same

1. I put 3 worker and 3 ps in a single machine. The Barrier() seems doesn't work. 
The wrong mesage is "[11:44:42] src/kvstore/././kvstore_dist_server.h:422: Check failed: !stored.is_none() init 82 first".
2. Then I try to put another Barrier() in 158, like below. The problem no longer occurs. 
```
if (!ps::Postoffice::Get()->is_recovery()) {
        std::cout<<keys[0]<<"-------------barrier-----------"<<ps::kWorkerGroup<<std::endl;
        Barrier();
        Barrier();
}
```

Why only one Barrier() seems doesn't work? 
@eric-haibin-lin

I don't think so?

```javascript
  addModelData(data) {
    const model = new Model(model, { resource: this });
    if (!this.models[model.id]) {
      this.models[model.id] = model;
    } else {
      this.models[model.id].set(model.attributes);
    }
    return this.models[model.id];
  }
```

Not a big deal – I just generally like to avoid overloading parameters in JS because the weak typing makes it harder to refactor later.

this needs to be outside of the `if headers` block, otherwise it will only be used if custome headers are specified.

if should be:
```python
if self.http_compress and body:
    body = gzip.compress(body)
```

@captainsafia where do you see that ipywidgets uses `_get_nbext_dir`? I can't find it, and it doesn't appear to be the case for any release of ipywidgets or current master.

@ellisonbg where have you seen private APIs being used across repos working on this PR? Any use of private APIs cross-repos should be considered a bug in the repo that's calling the private API. I think we've mostly done a good job improving our public/private distinctions now that we should only be consuming our own public APIs between repos.

> We need to come with a firm official policy on this and start stick to it.

I think we already have by splitting the repos: we shouldn't use private APIs across repos.

Suggestion: let's get rid of the `ptr` here and we can do this instead:
```
    return SendPropertyUpdate(
                 header,
                 SPINEL_CMD_PROP_VALUE_IS,
                 key,
                 SPINEL_DATATYPE_DATA_S,
                 otThreadGetMasterKey(mInstance)->m8,
                 OT_MASTER_KEY_SIZE
             );
  }
```

I think the right check should be:
```
if (model.ir_version() >= 3) {
  // enforce opset_imports is not empty
} else {
  // enforce opset_imports is empty,
  // and set the default value for ONNX_DOMAIN
}
```
